---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="School Visits & Contact Info - Kat Falls"
  description="School, library, conference, and book club presentation information for Kat Falls, including AV needs, Skype visits, and ordering details."
>
  <section class="bg-brand-dark text-brand-warm py-20">
    <div class="section-container">
      <p class="section-subheading text-brand-gold">School, Library & Book Club Presentations</p>
      <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-serif mb-4">School Visits &amp; Contact Info</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-brand-warm/80 max-w-3xl leading-relaxed">
        Kat enjoys speaking about her books and writing process, and she is comfortable doing presentations for groups of any size.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-container grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-12">
    <div class="md:col-span-2 space-y-10">
      <div>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-brand-dark mb-4">Presentations</h2>
        <div class="space-y-5 text-brand-dark/75 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            Kat is willing to create a specific program to suit the needs of a conference, book club, library, or school. Her presentations are generally 45 minutes long, but can be tailored to fit the time available.
          </p>
          <p>
            During her talk, Kat tries to get teen and tween readers excited about books and writing. She discusses how she comes up with story ideas and how much research goes into writing a science fiction novel. She also shares behind-the-scenes stories about her journey to publication.
          </p>
          <p>
            Throughout the presentation, Kat shows projected images from her research that inspired and informed her middle grade <em>Dark Life</em> series and her young adult <em>Inhuman</em> series, including deep-sea creatures, future technology, and cutting edge science. These images always generate lots of questions from students and help keep the program lively and interactive. Afterwards, Kat is available for book signing and conversation.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="bg-white border border-brand-dark/10 rounded-sm shadow-sm p-6">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl text-brand-dark mb-3">Fees</h3>
          <p class="text-brand-dark/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Email Kat directly for information on honorarium fees:
          </p>
          <a
            href="mailto:katfalls77@gmail.com"
            class="inline-block mt-3 text-brand-accent font-semibold hover:underline"
          >
            katfalls77@gmail.com
          </a>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-brand-dark/10 rounded-sm shadow-sm p-6">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl text-brand-dark mb-3">AV Tech Needs</h3>
          <p class="text-brand-dark/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Kat has her PowerPoint presentation on a flash drive and therefore needs a computer attached to a projector and a screen. She also hopes for a good microphone if she is speaking to a large group.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="bg-brand-warm/50 border border-brand-dark/10 rounded-sm p-6">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl text-brand-dark mb-3">Conferences &amp; Book Festivals</h3>
          <p class="text-brand-dark/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Kat enjoys being on panels with other authors as well as giving solo presentations. She is also comfortable leading a workshop or breakout session on craft.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-brand-warm/50 border border-brand-dark/10 rounded-sm p-6">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl text-brand-dark mb-3">Skype Visits</h3>
          <p class="text-brand-dark/70 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Skype visits are always free. Send an email to
            <a href="mailto:katfalls77@gmail.com" class="text-brand-accent hover:underline">katfalls77@gmail.com</a>
            with a proposed date and time, and put <strong>SKYPE REQUEST</strong> in the subject line.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-brand-dark text-brand-warm rounded-sm p-6">
        <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl mb-3">Ordering Books</h3>
        <p class="text-brand-warm/75 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          You can order Kat's books from your nearby bookstore, or schools and libraries can order at a discounted rate through the Scholastic Teacher Store.
        </p>
        <a
          href="https://shop.scholastic.com/teachers-ecommerce/teacher"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          class="inline-block mt-4 text-brand-gold font-semibold hover:underline"
        >
          Visit the Scholastic Teacher Store -&gt;
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <aside class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-white border border-brand-dark/10 rounded-sm shadow-sm p-6">
        <p class="section-subheading">Quick Snapshot</p>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-brand-dark mb-4">What Kat Can Do</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-brand-dark/70">
          <li>45-minute talks that can be tailored to your schedule.</li>
          <li>School, library, conference, and book club presentations.</li>
          <li>Projected research images that connect books to science.</li>
          <li>Interactive Q&amp;A plus signing and conversation afterward.</li>
          <li>Workshop and breakout session leadership for writing craft.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border border-brand-dark/10 rounded-sm shadow-sm p-6">
        <p class="section-subheading">Best Fit</p>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-brand-dark mb-4">Topics Students Love</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm text-brand-dark/70">
          <li>How story ideas begin.</li>
          <li>How research shapes science fiction.</li>
          <li>The path from idea to publication.</li>
          <li>Deep-sea life, future tech, and strange science.</li>
          <li>Writing adventure for tween and teen readers.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-brand-accent text-white rounded-sm p-6">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl mb-3">Direct Contact</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-white/85 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Email Kat directly for school visits, conference invitations, Skype requests, and presentation questions.
        </p>
        <a href="mailto:katfalls77@gmail.com" class="font-semibold underline">katfalls77@gmail.com</a>
      </div>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-brand-warm/50 py-16">
    <div class="section-container grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
      <div>
        <p class="section-subheading">In Person</p>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-brand-dark mb-4">School and Library Visits</h2>
        <p class="text-brand-dark/70 leading-relaxed">
          Kat is comfortable speaking to groups of any size and can adapt her presentation for one class, a library audience, a full school assembly, or a conference setting.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="section-subheading">Virtual</p>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-brand-dark mb-4">Free Skype Requests</h2>
        <p class="text-brand-dark/70 leading-relaxed">
          For schools or readers who want a shorter online option, Skype visits are always free. Send a proposed date and time by email and include <strong>SKYPE REQUEST</strong> in the subject line.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
